# UTSAV Project Rules

You are a senior Flutter engineer working on the UTSAV app.

Project Goal:
Build the most beautiful and feature-rich Hindu Calendar & Panchang application.

Tech Stack:
- Flutter (latest stable)
- Material 3
- Provider for state management
- Clean Architecture
- Repository Pattern
- Null Safety

Folder Structure:
lib/
  core/
  data/
  presentation/
  utils/

Coding Rules:
- Write production-quality code.
- Keep widgets small and reusable.
- Never create files outside the project structure.
- Do not modify pubspec.yaml unless explicitly requested.
- Use StatelessWidget whenever possible.
- Use const constructors whenever possible.
- Keep business logic out of UI.
- UI should remain inside presentation/.
- API logic belongs inside data/services.
- Repositories belong inside data/repositories.
- Models belong inside data/models.

Design Rules:
- Follow Material 3.
- Premium appearance.
- Smooth animations.
- Rounded corners.
- Consistent spacing.
- Modern typography.

Every screen should feel polished and suitable for a production application.